               <head>'Attar's Tazkirat ul-auliya'</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Taz̲kirat al-awliyāʾ by ʿAṭṭār, Farīd al-Dīn, -approximately 1230</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91002492 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16775-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>The famous biographical work on the lives, virtues and sayings of early Sufis. By Farīd al-Dīn ‘Aṭṭār (d. ca. 1220). See Storey PL I/2, pp. 930-933. The present manuscript is the earliest known dated copy. </p>
                        <p>Completed in 686/1287, at the khānaqāh of <persName key="person_f7441" role="oth">Najīb al-Dīn ‘Alī ibn Burghush</persName>. Copied by <persName key="person_f7162" role="scr">Ḥasan ibn Muḥammad ibn Abī Bakr al-Khalīlī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Excellent early naskhī. Red headings. 19 lines. Illuminated title frontispiece, 1r, and Basmala heading, 1v. 266 folios. 26 x 18 cm. Good brown morocco binding, ca. 9th/15th century. </p>
                        <p>Purchased from Christies (6 October 2009, Lot 64). </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21126">Taz̲kirat al-awliyāʾ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21126">تذكرة الاولياء</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100000000818.0x000215 viaf_120724759">ʿAṭṭār, Farīd al-Dīn, -approximately 1230</persName>
                        <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100000000818.0x000215 viaf_120724759" xml:lang="per">‏عطار، فريد الدين محمد بن ابراهيم نيشابورى</persName>
